For Loop

A `for` loop is used when the number of iterations is known.

syntax

```cpp
for (initialization; condition; update) {
    // code
}
```

example

```cpp
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    cout << i << " ";
}
}
```

**output**

```bash
1 2 3 4 5
```

```text
For Loop Flow
1. Initialization
2. Condition Check
3. Execute Body
4. Update
5. Repeat
```

> [!note]  
> The loop executes as long as the condition is true.

Print "xnocode" 5 times

```cpp
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    cout << "xnocode" << endl;
}
}
```

Print numbers from 1 to n

```cpp
