Loop inside a loop

```bash
 1  1  1  1  <-- R1
 2  2  2  2  <-- R2
 3  3  3  3  <-- R3
 4  4  4  4  <-- R4
 C1 C2 C3 C4

 C -> column
 R -> row
```

If you want to understand nested loop we should practice pattern so that we got clear understanding

1. Outer loop : no of rows
2. inner loop : no of columns
3. works in inner loop: each row

```cpp
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
	//outer loop
	for(int i=1; i<=4; i++){
		//inner loop
		for(int j=1; j<=4; j++){
			//work
			cout << i << " ";
		}
		cout << endl;
	}
}
```

